						               													<description>Azione Violenta su Barcellona is a small and simple Solitaire postcard wargame published as a freebie by SNAFU Design, as a gift to customers of SNAFU Store, and as a free downloadable PnP file.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It's a game on the &amp;ldquo;carpet bombing&amp;rdquo; campaign carried out by the Italian &amp;ldquo;Aviazione Legionaria&amp;rdquo; on March 16, 17 and 18, 1938. The campaign was carried out through over a dozen of daylight attacks by Savoia Marchetti SM.79s of the 8th Group &amp;ldquo;Falchi delle Baleari&amp;rdquo; and night-time bombardments by Savoia Marchetti SM.81s of the XXV Autonomous Night Bombing Group &amp;ldquo;Pipistrelli delle Baleari&amp;rdquo; taking off from Mallorca.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player must plan in advance their air raids to some sectors of the city with the airplanes available each turn and manage to demoralize the city of Barcelona in a maximum of six turns. Failing to do this by the end turn 6 is a loss, which is the historical result. While the bombardments did inflict a lot of casualties and physical damage to the buildings and infrastructures, the population barely fled Barcelona, nor took the streets to force the government to capitulate.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
